<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="then-adv">then <strong><em>adv</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ðen/    美 /ðen/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(指过去) 当时；(指将来) 到那时：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>Just then</strong> she opened her eyes and gave him a smile.
正好那时她睁开眼睛冲他微笑了一下。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We shall have left school then.
到那时我们就毕业了。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>然后；接着：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Byron travelled to Italy and then to Greece.
拜伦先去意大利旅行，然后去了希腊。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>那么：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If I expect you to be punctual, then I should be punctual first.
如果我要求你准时，那么首先我就应该准时。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>另外；还有：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She has been very busy at work and then there was all that trouble with her son.
她工作一直很忙，另外还有儿子的一大堆麻烦事。</p></div></div>